BEGIN NOW Ever since I heard of Datura from a friend at school a few years ago, I have always tried to get a hold of some, asking dealers I knew from around town. END
BEGIN NOW But I was never successful, as many people I asked didn't even know what it was. END
BEGIN NOW So after awhile I gave up hope and continued with the usual, smoking grass everyday, occasionally scoring some ketamine or opium to make life a little more interesting. END
BEGIN NOW Then last year I finally got a chance to try the stuff. END
BEGIN NOW One of my friends told me he had gone to stay with his grandparents for a week and noticed a plant near their house that looked a lot like Datura, so he went over to it and sure enough he saw the small, spikey pods growing near the bottom of the plant. END
BEGIN NOW He himself didnt want to try any because he always feared any sort of hallucinogen because of the risk of a bad trip, but knew I had been wanting to try it for quite some time, so he picked one of the magical pods and wrapped it up in cellophane and brought them back for me. END
BEGIN NOW The bastard wouldnt hand them over unless I paid him 20 bucks, but I figured it would be well worth it. END
BEGIN NOW I couldnt wait to try them. END
BEGIN NOW First thing I did was found someone who would be a sitter for me, and that sitter was the most trustworthy friend I know (lets call him Steve). END
BEGIN NOW I asked my mom if he could sleep over and she said it was fine. END
BEGIN NOW So the next day, Steve came over around noon, and I got the seeds out of the pod and counted 37. END
BEGIN NOW I heard it only took like 10 or 15, and I wanted to have more so I could trip another time or sell them, so I decided to take 15. END
BEGIN NOW T:00.00 - Me and Steve went up to my room to take them. END
BEGIN NOW We put on some music and sat down in my bean bag chairs. END
BEGIN NOW I was feeling confident that things were going to go smoothly, mostly just because Steve was there with me, he was a very responsible person who I felt very safe and secure with. END
BEGIN NOW Of course I had a little butterflies in my stomach because I was taking something new, but it was mostly excitement, a total 'I cant wait' feeling. END
BEGIN NOW As Steve and I talked, I decided it was time, and pulled the sandwich baggie out of my pocket. END
BEGIN NOW I got all the seeds in my palm and looked at them, little teardrop shaped things, darkish brown, almost black. END
BEGIN NOW I thought to my self 'here goes nothing' and licked my palm to get all the seeds stuck on my tongue, chewed em up a bit, and swallowed. END
BEGIN NOW As they went down I got this overwhelming feeling of 'finally'. END
BEGIN NOW I have finally taken this crazy Datura, and in time I will be experiencing it. END
BEGIN NOW All I could do now is relax, keep the best state of mind I possibly could, and wait for things to kick in. END
BEGIN NOW T:00.30 - Went down to the kitchen with Steve to get a drink of water, and then went to the bathroom. END
BEGIN NOW No noticeable effects. END
BEGIN NOW Steve suggested we play video games while we wait for it to kick in. END
BEGIN NOW We went back to my room and played Mario Kart 64 and snacked on some doritos. END
BEGIN NOW T:00.50 - Starting to feel different. END
BEGIN NOW A lot like when you need to stretch really bad, but in my whole body. END
BEGIN NOW Mouth is getting dry, very similar to the cottonmouth after smoking a thick blunt. END
BEGIN NOW Steve is winning the game and I am loosing my grip on the controller, and I cant seem to keep the A button pushed down. END
BEGIN NOW After about 10 minutes I feel much different, very intense, and Im wondering why Steve is in my room playing video games. END
BEGIN NOW He reminds me that he is sleeping over to watch me because I took Datura. END
BEGIN NOW Right after he says this a wave of shock and fear run down my body like goosebumps, for I had completely forgotten the reason he was there, and that I had taken anything, although I do recall it, I am needless to say in shock at what just happened with my brain. END
BEGIN NOW I look at Steve and say 'calm me down', and somehow, Steve knew exactly what to do. END
BEGIN NOW He just smiled at me in this reassuring smile and said 'dont worry man, youre gonna have a blast' this made me feel incredibly better, and my mood shifted. END
BEGIN NOW After this, things seem to go back to normal, and I ask Steve to stop playing video games and go downstairs with me. END
BEGIN NOW We go downstairs into my kitchen and I pull a full pitcher of cherry kool-aid from the fridge. END
BEGIN NOW Steve got 2 glasses, then we went into my living room and sat down on the couch. END
BEGIN NOW I pour the both of us a glass and we sip it while watching tv. END
BEGIN NOW Afer I finish my glass I pick up the pitcher and gulp it down halfway. END
BEGIN NOW I am very thirsty, but the drink doesnt seem to quench my thirst at all, it seems to glide over the surface of my mouth, leaving it dry still. END
BEGIN NOW I now just try my best to ignore it, and continue watching tv. END
BEGIN NOW T:01:30 I tell Steve Ill be right back, and walk to the bathroom. END
BEGIN NOW While I piss I look at this picture above my toilet. END
BEGIN NOW Its a cartoon of a polar bear lying on its back in the water, holding a wine glass like it fell asleep from being drunk. END
BEGIN NOW The concept makes me want to laugh, it seems like the dumbest cartoon in the world to me, and its location is just as random as its contents. END
BEGIN NOW I think to my self 'why the f*** do we have a picture of a drunk polar bear in our bathroom'. END
BEGIN NOW For some reason, this seems near hysterical to me. END
BEGIN NOW I walk out of the bathroom and go back to the couch with Steve. END
BEGIN NOW As soon as I sit down, my mom walked out of the kitchen and tells us shes going to work and to behave, shell be back around 10. END
BEGIN NOW Steve and I say good bye and she leaves. END
BEGIN NOW Perfect. END
BEGIN NOW Now we have the house to ourselves. END
BEGIN NOW T:02:00 - Nothing much more seems to be happening. END
BEGIN NOW I have finished the pitcher of kool-aid and gone to the bathroom 2 more times. END
BEGIN NOW Steve says to go in the kitchen and refill the pitcher with water in case I feel like Im going to dehydrate. END
BEGIN NOW It seems like a responsible idea so I go into the kitchen and refill it with water and put ice cubes in it. END
BEGIN NOW I walk back into my living room to find Steve has left, and the tv has been turned off. END
BEGIN NOW The entire house is dead silent. END
BEGIN NOW Then I hear the tv go back on, but the screen is blank, and I hear Steve saying 'hey Im over here'. END
BEGIN NOW I realize that hes calling me from out in my backyard, so I put my shoes on and go outside. END
BEGIN NOW At first I scanned my back yard for him, but couldnt see him, and I couldnt hear him anymore. END
BEGIN NOW I suddenly get the idea that Steve had come over for a hide and seek game (at this point I have absolutely no idea that I have taken anything) so I run into the yard looking around for him. END
BEGIN NOW Then I speak 'come out come out where ever you are' . END
BEGIN NOW Right when I say this my voice sounds very different, like a person who has gone totally insane. END
BEGIN NOW This starts to scare me very much, and Steve is nowhere to be found. END
BEGIN NOW I look way across to the other end of my yard (my yard is only about a 100 foot by 200 foot area, but now it was a soccer field size) and at the other end I see my dogs pen, a fenced in area in the corner with all my friends who are straight edge that stopped being friends with me when I started smoking pot. END
BEGIN NOW I havent seen them in so long, so I run towards the pen. END
BEGIN NOW They look just as happy to see me as I am to see them, and they let me into the pen. END
BEGIN NOW We start talking and to my surprise, one of them pulls a blunt out of nowhere and sparks it. END
BEGIN NOW I am naturally amused but shocked, then they start to explain to me that they came to see me cause they all 'got into the game' and dont think drugs are that bad after all. END
BEGIN NOW On the outside I am pleased to hear this, but on the inside I begin to get feelings of untrust. END
BEGIN NOW These bastards abandoned me years back. END
BEGIN NOW I dont show any unpleasant feelings on the outside, and I continue to be cheery with them, although I keep a state of mind not to trust anyone there. END
BEGIN NOW They pass me the blunt and I take a super long hit, and hold it super long and blow out. END
BEGIN NOW After it went around a few times we all spark a cigarette to increase our high. END
BEGIN NOW We just keep talking and talking. END
BEGIN NOW It seems like time has stopped. END
BEGIN NOW How long can people just sit here and talk? END
BEGIN NOW Its been hours, I think to myself (strangely enough I am still puffing on the same cigarette, but dont notice anything unusual about it). END
BEGIN NOW Then I drop my butt, and it falls under the chair Im sitting on. END
BEGIN NOW 'Ah Shit' I said and got out of my seat to get it. END
BEGIN NOW I look under the chair but I cant seem to find it. END
BEGIN NOW 'Did any of you see were my...' as I turn around I notice no one is there, and I am alone in the pen. END
BEGIN NOW A sense of anger comes over me, and I get intense feelings of 'I shouldnt have trusted them' and 'how dare they'. END
BEGIN NOW These feelings are followed by loneliness and then total fear. END
BEGIN NOW I need to get out of this pen and go back in the house. END
BEGIN NOW I walk back to my house across the long field, and it seems to take even longer to go back than when I had come. END
BEGIN NOW Next thing I know Im back in my kitchen lying on the floor very sweaty, Steve is there sitting on the kitchen counter. END
BEGIN NOW My focus is very blurred and 'off' and I feel very confused about why hes there on the counter and Im on the floor, but every few moments I kinda snap back into reality and know exactly what going on, then snap back into delirium and totally forget everything. END
BEGIN NOW Next thing I know its already 6:46am and I am running late. END
BEGIN NOW My mom tells me I only got a half hour to get ready or ill get a Saturday detention. END
BEGIN NOW I scramble out of bed and run into the bathroom to take a shower. END
BEGIN NOW I suddenly realize how mush schools gonna suck cause I forgot to do my homework and I have an oral presentation due today. END
BEGIN NOW All these thoughts make me panic and I know theres no way out of it cause I already skipped school 3 times this year and got caught and I cant skip another day or I have to go to court. END
BEGIN NOW I get out of the shower and dry off as quickly as I can. END
BEGIN NOW Then I run into my room and get dressed and go downstairs to the kitchen. END
BEGIN NOW Right then I noticed something was wrong, the clock said 1:00am and the calendar was on July. END
BEGIN NOW No body was up. END
BEGIN NOW My mom was asleep and had been asleep. END
BEGIN NOW She didnt wake me up for school, I did not have school in summer. END
BEGIN NOW I wished I was dreaming, and the thoughts in my mind were on the brink of driving me insane. END
BEGIN NOW All I remember after this is running back up into my room in total panic ready to cry and scream and if one more weird thing happened I was gonna commit suicide. END
BEGIN NOW I woke up in my bed with Steve on the floor watching me, he looked very concerned and asked me if I was ok now, if I was still tripping. END
BEGIN NOW I didnt know what to say to him, cause right then I could have still be tripping for all I know. END
BEGIN NOW It was 5:00pm the next day, I had a bad headache and couldnt focus on shit, and my whole body was in this dreadfully uncomfortable state. END
BEGIN NOW It took me awhile to collect my thoughts and figure out I was not tripping anymore, and I had these series of very strange realistic dreams stuck in my head from when I was asleep, but I cant for the life of me remember what they were now, I forgot them completely about 4 hours after I woke up. END
BEGIN NOW From Steves point of view, in a nutshell, I had started acting weird when I had gotten the water from the kitchen. END
BEGIN NOW He said that he was trying to talk to me but I would just have this blank stare like I couldnt see him, and then ran outside into my shed in the backyard and started talking to myself, and after an hour or so I ran out of the shed with this scared shitless look on my face and fell down, and crawled back into the house, into the bathroom and he said I was trying to drink out of the toilet, he pulled me up and carried me into the kitchen and put down on the floor and got some ice for me. END
BEGIN NOW He said I was talking in my sleep and saying random words in no logical order whatsoever but I was saying them fluently like I knew what I was talking about. END
BEGIN NOW Before my mom came home, he carried me upstairs and put me to bed, and stayed up to watch me, and he said I was talking out loud and moving around like I was having nightmares, and around midnight I sprang out of bed and ran into the bathroom and got in the shower for an hour and then went back into my room and put a shirt on backwards and some boxers but no pants and ran downstairs and stood in the kitchen for 10 minutes, just standing there. END
BEGIN NOW He said then I freaked out and ran upstairs into my room and he said he had to push me onto my bed and hold me down until I stopped moving, and eventually fell asleep, then he did. END
BEGIN NOW He woke up around 10 that day and I slept till 5. END
BEGIN NOW To sum it up in one word...insanity. END
BEGIN NOW Thats what if feels like if you start to snap out of it and realize whats happening, but then you just go back into this state of total confusion and its enough to drive anyone crazy. END
BEGIN NOW Overall I am glad I experienced this, just to know what its like, but this is not for everyone, and Im not saying the experience was at all pleasant, so I have no motivation to do it again anytime soon, maybe someday years from now just for some crazy fun. END
BEGIN NOW But this Datura seems to be something not of this world. END
BEGIN NOW The hallucinations were accompanied by delirium and confusion which made them seem real and like I wasnt really tripping. END
BEGIN NOW This stuff truly is THE DEVILS WEED. END
BEGIN NOW So... END
BEGIN NOW I decided to take Datura orally for the first time at Burning Man in 2006. END
BEGIN NOW A couple months earlier I had smoked the flowers for the first time with my mother, and she had sent me off to the desert with a Ziploc full of dried leaves and flowers. END
BEGIN NOW Smoking the flowers, as others have reported is a slightly less relaxing buzz than that of marijuana (though surprisingly similar). END
BEGIN NOW Given the choice, I think I'd always pick marijuana, because it tastes better and it's less edgy. END
BEGIN NOW Anyhow, fast forward to Black Rock City, a few days into the burn. END
BEGIN NOW I'm there with my sister, 3 year old nephew and girlfriend of many years. END
BEGIN NOW We decide that I'll be the first to do this, and perhaps that they will try some the next night, depending on how it goes for me. END
BEGIN NOW I make sun tea out of the flowers, stems and leaves by stuffing a bunch of them into a waterbottle, and sitting it on top of the van until the sun goes down. END
BEGIN NOW I mix some up with a chai tea, and do my best to get it down. END
BEGIN NOW A pretty foul brew, and of course I make that choice I always recognize as foolish later - after my initial dose, and waiting for a short while, I feel nothing and decide to pour myself another dose. END
BEGIN NOW Almost immediately, the first dose kicks in. END
BEGIN NOW Considering the anti-emetic effects, I am lucky to vomit almost right away before it becomes impossible, kicking out some of that second dose before it piles on top of the first one. END
BEGIN NOW There's a process of being taken to the porta-potties and back to camp by my g/f. END
BEGIN NOW At this point, I'm having difficulty tracking the proper direction to and from these destinations, and an intense, horrid thirst. END
BEGIN NOW Absolutely the most parched I've ever felt in my life, and I don't have my water bottle with me during the trek. END
BEGIN NOW It's not pleasant in the least, and I'm squeezing my g/fs hand very hard, being mean and cranky and difficult to sit for, constantly pulling her off course and complaining loudly about how frustratingly thirsty I am as we make this little journey. END
BEGIN NOW Fortunately, this was probably the worst part of the whole experience, and things began to get better as soon as I managed to get back to camp and ingest some fluids. END
BEGIN NOW Nonetheless, things are coming on strong, with a lot of body buzz. END
BEGIN NOW After a small bit of exploring in camp, including apparently unsuccessful attempts to touch the pink flamingo attached to the van antenna, I decide that before I'm ready to deal with the world in this new state, I'm going to need to lie down in the van on the mattress and relax under the covers, and get used to my body. END
BEGIN NOW As I say to my companions, 'I feel like my feet are made out of something other than feet'. END
BEGIN NOW I spend some time in the dark, expecting the kalidescope fractals of other hallucinogens, but there's actually very little of this. END
BEGIN NOW I spend a bit of time reading (I think it was Hitchhikers Guide to the Galaxy, but it may have been Inifinite Jest - I really can't remember at this point, except that it was one of my two large blue books, so it had to be one of them) and discover the visual distortion that will follow me through the evening. END
BEGIN NOW To wit, everything appears to be about six inches closer to me than it actually is (explaining my failure to make contact with the flamingo earlier that so amused my companions). END
BEGIN NOW I discover this because I'm unable to read my book with my glasses on, but if I take them off and hold the book at a normal distance, I'm able to read the book just as I would if I were holding it too close to my face with them off. END
BEGIN NOW Now, after a bit of accustoming myself to my new world, I get up out of bed and decide that it's time to play. END
BEGIN NOW My sister and g/f are not in camp when I climb out of the van and, reflecting on how unpleasant the trip to the bathroom with the g/f had been, decided to throw caution to the wind and left camp without a babysitter. END
BEGIN NOW When I eventually returned, I discovered that this had, of course, totally throw them for a loop, and that my g/f had a pretty good panic and went hunting for me, unsuccessfully. END
BEGIN NOW Once I set out on foot, I found that, while still present, the sensation of increased gravity began to lift away and my spirits rose. END
BEGIN NOW Other than the issue of depth perception, which made it seem to the people around me that I was trying to pet the things I was really trying to reach for, I didn't have the noticeable fluid visual hallucinations associate with many other hallucinogens. END
BEGIN NOW But, with the fact that I was at Burning Man of all places, and my lack of a babysitter to corroborate my story with, I frankly have no idea what I saw and heard that was real and what was purely a construct of my mind, making it hard to piece together a narrative of my experiences. END
BEGIN NOW I definitely experienced some disorientation, occasionally wandering into other peoples camps inappropriately. END
BEGIN NOW I was also subject to the phantom cigarettes and other items that so many other users report. END
BEGIN NOW In my case, I also had a phantom water bottle. END
BEGIN NOW I suspect that this phenomenon, while most commonly reported with the cigarettes, is actually something that is a user subjective occurence based on whatever repetetive actions they commonly perform. END
BEGIN NOW This would explain the water bottle for me (as keeping hydrated is the most common repetetive action I have going on out there on the Playa), and what I've heard for other people, like gamers who will fall into playing a game with a phantom controller. END
BEGIN NOW I had an extensive conversation with one fellow sitting under the scavenger hunt board, who I assumed was real, and a few other people encounters, but I do not recall imagining meetings with people I know, which seems to be something most people do run into. END
BEGIN NOW Instead, the most unusual effect is that I had what I can only call hallucinatory memories. END
BEGIN NOW I would find myself acting on a memory of something said or done, only to realize that not only had I not actually had the conversation or taken the action that triggered what I was doing, but that I hadn't even hallucinated the conversation or action, but that I was remembering something I had not experienced at all. END
BEGIN NOW Disconcerting, to say the least! END
BEGIN NOW One such scenario happened as I was trying to find my way back to our camp, and realized that I was bearing in the wrong direction, because I remembered distinctly having a discussion with someone about how a whole row of sites had been moved one row further out. END
BEGIN NOW Suddenly I realized that there was no way that would have happened, and that the conversation hadn't actually happened, nor had I even experienced a hallucinatory conversation, and that I was remembering something completely false. END
BEGIN NOW I also spent quite some time searching for my bicycle, which I had distinct memories of leaving... somewhere. END
BEGIN NOW In a very dreamlike state, I would wander looking for it, lose track of my self, start doing something else and then remember that I needed to find my bike. END
BEGIN NOW Eventually I gave it up for lost, and I did make it back to camp and reassured everyone that I was still alive and OK. END
BEGIN NOW I had never had my bike with me, it was in camp the whole time. END
BEGIN NOW After a bit, I decided that I had had probably about enough of Datura world, so I took 25mg of Trazodone which put me to sleep and allowed me to sleep well into the heat of the next day. END
BEGIN NOW Normally, I hate using Trazodone as a sleep aid, as it tends to require a very long window in which to rest (12-16 hours), or I'm unable to function the next day, but in this case, that was just what I needed. END
BEGIN NOW The next day I was still mildly disassociated, but I didn't have the multiday ongoing trip that many users report. END
BEGIN NOW Again, I think I was probably pretty fortunate to vomit early on, or I expect I would have had an even longer stranger trip. END
BEGIN NOW I haven't taken an oral dosage of it since, but I found my experience to be pretty positive overall, and have definitely considered doing it again. END
BEGIN NOW The environment I was in was, I think, a big part of why it was so positive - I can see why taking this drug around a lot of straight folks in a real city, instead of the sea of freaks in a temporary city, might be overwhelming and much more difficult to maintain. END
BEGIN NOW Running off without my sitter was unwise, and a bit rude of me, but I don't think I would have enjoyed that particular individual sitting me for the trip, so it turned out to be a good thing. END
BEGIN NOW If I do it again, I think I'd really like to have a partner in the experience to compare with, as well as a sober sitter to keep an eye on us. END
BEGIN NOW Both my girlfriend and sister chose not to imbibe, but I believe I was able to pass some on to another burner, though I don't recall ever getting any feedback from him on how it went. END
BEGIN NOW What follows are the events of my first two experimental Datura trips. END
BEGIN NOW Im a 21 year old, 200 pound male experienced psychonaut, having used nearly all common psychedelics multiple times, as well as all but one 2C chemical. END
BEGIN NOW Im an uncanny hard head to most psychedelic compounds (much to my dismay) which means I can rarely achieve the level of experience as many other experience report authors, unless taking an immensely high dose. END
BEGIN NOW The Datura inoxia I used was found on my college campus, and it is definitely a genuine, native specimen. END
BEGIN NOW I have spent much of this year researching and reading on the tropane alkaloid containing plants (Datura, belladonna, mandrake, brugmansia, and henbane to name a few). END
BEGIN NOW I had my heart set on belladonna, but recently I discovered a perfectly good Datura shrub, and that gave me the inspiration to begin. END
BEGIN NOW Both of these experiments were done indoors, in a large house with 21 members. END
BEGIN NOW They were all good friends, and a few of them knew what I was planning to do. END
BEGIN NOW I chose two experienced trip sitters to read a handful of Datura trip reports and the Datura-sitting guidelines, just in case things went sour. END
BEGIN NOW Experiment one: 

T-0:00 (3:00pm): Ground up 50 small Datura inoxia seeds in a mortar and pestle. END
BEGIN NOW The seed coats are exceedingly durable, and the mortar and pestle did very little to truly crush them. END
BEGIN NOW Moisture was expelled from them only after a long period of crushing. END
BEGIN NOW I chewed them as much as I could, and washed them down with water. END
BEGIN NOW Despite intense bitterness, I was able to choke them down with minimal gagging. END
BEGIN NOW This is a test run for me; I find it highly unlikely that the small dose will affect me. END
BEGIN NOW Fortunately, you can always take more after the fact, but you can never take less. END
BEGIN NOW At 200 pounds, this may be one of the smallest dose to weight ratios for which there is a plausible experience report. END
BEGIN NOW T+0:50: Ive begun to feel the gradual placebo come up; something I often feel when very anxious about a new drug. END
BEGIN NOW Its nearly certainly psychological, but to enhance the feeling, I smoked 10 seeds of Datura Inoxia out of a waterless bong. END
BEGIN NOW They smoke surprisingly well, and the taste, although slightly acrid, isnt entirely unpleasant. END
BEGIN NOW Its difficult to inhale once a certain smoke volume is reached, and the seeds taste much like a cross between burning marshmallow and gasoline. END
BEGIN NOW Taking large bong rips is completely out of the question due to the power of the smoke. END
BEGIN NOW The smoking has elicited a rather dry mouth, as expected, but only slight changes in perception. END
BEGIN NOW T+1:00: Another 10 seeds were smoked, this time with water added to the bong. END
BEGIN NOW This markedly increased the volume able to be inhaled. END
BEGIN NOW Sensory effects have begun to grow, but only slightly. END
BEGIN NOW T+2:00: Ive been trying to sleep for the last hour and surprisingly it was a comfortable nap. END
BEGIN NOW However, the effects were very faint. END
BEGIN NOW I had difficulty focusing on things, much like trying to view something after staring at the sun for a while. END
BEGIN NOW But the one way I knew that it was working was the dry mouth and throat; it was completely impossible to rehydrate; water simply seemed to run off the dry lining of my throat rather than absorbing into it. END
BEGIN NOW T+4:00 no new effects have cropped up, aside from more noticeable dry throat and an increase in epidermal discomfort; I felt as though I was wearing a wool jumpsuit with nothing over it. END
BEGIN NOW My friend and I cooked a delicious pizza, but I found it to be tasteless and dry due to the supreme lack of saliva in my mouth. END
BEGIN NOW It filled me up, but didnt grant me even the slightest pleasure. END
BEGIN NOW T+6:00: I feel to be coming down already which is uncommon according to most Datura trip reports. END
BEGIN NOW The sore throat has gotten markedly better, my vision is slightly off kilter but barely noticeably so, and the skin irritation is no longer present. END
BEGIN NOW Ill probably call it a night early, and for the next experiment, either double the seed dose and/or smoke the leaves and roots. END
BEGIN NOW A tea may also help. END
BEGIN NOW T+14:00: Feel much better this morning, although it has reminded me of how unpleasant the earlier night had been. END
BEGIN NOW Im certainly not looking forward to upping the dosage... END
BEGIN NOW Experience 2: 

T-0:00: I chose to up the dosage considerably on my second experiment with Datura, picking one fresh flower, four fresh leaves, and roughly 300 seeds. END
BEGIN NOW I pulverized them all in a mortar and pestle until there was a soggy wad. END
BEGIN NOW This wad was added to 1.5 cups of boiling water, and I allowed fifteen minutes to elapse for the solution to concentrate and release the tropane alkaloids. END
BEGIN NOW One cup of the water evaporated in the boiling process, leaving 12 cup. END
BEGIN NOW I strained this with a coffee filter into another cup filled with lemonade and fruit punch. END
BEGIN NOW In this mixture, the Datura wasnt even noticeable. END
BEGIN NOW T+1:00: The dry mouth is already in full swing, and by body does not feel good at all. END
BEGIN NOW There are pins and needles all over me, and no amount of rubbing helps. END
BEGIN NOW I have also grown extremely unbalanced, almost exactly how I feel while intoxicated with alcohol. END
BEGIN NOW I generally am holding on to something as I wander around my house, to keep from tripping (physically). END
BEGIN NOW T+2:00: Ive fallen into some sort of hypnotic hibernation. END
BEGIN NOW I feel too lousy to walk around, my eyes hurt too much to open, and the spring water I drink is indistinguishable from puddle water. END
BEGIN NOW So I sit on my love sack, eyes closed, body intensely irritated. END
BEGIN NOW At one point, needing to go to the bathroom, I got up and swayed my way to the toilet. END
BEGIN NOW In my experience, walking while on Datura is much like walking blindfolded in a boulder field. END
BEGIN NOW Its impossible to tell when my feet are going to land on the ground. END
BEGIN NOW Occasionally it felt as though I was walking with one foot on the sidewalk and one on the road. END
BEGIN NOW Urination is highly abnormal: I pee for much longer than average, but the volume expelled is significantly smaller. END
BEGIN NOW Also, after finishing, I feel like I need to go even worse than before. END
BEGIN NOW T+3:00: I believe I finally got into bed at this point, and that is where the trip truly started. END
BEGIN NOW Its very difficult to explain, but I began to have the ability to switch between reality and dreams. END
BEGIN NOW One minute, in my minds eye, Id be sitting in a field, speaking to a friend or two (in my head, not out loud). END
BEGIN NOW Id jerk my eyes open and return swiftly to lying in bed. END
BEGIN NOW But the second my eyes closed again, there I was in an entirely new setting. END
BEGIN NOW The most incredible thing about these dream hallucinations was the speed with which they unraveled. END
BEGIN NOW I was literally having about six small dreams a minute, ranging from a quick brusque conversation to weeding a garden. END
BEGIN NOW Despite how mundane they were, it was always very peculiar to choose when to awake. END
BEGIN NOW I wouldnt call these lucid dreams, because I was not in control of what I was dreaming; I could only manipulate the point when I started and when I ended the dream. END
BEGIN NOW Very few times, during what I assume were slightly more realistic dreams, I even woke myself up by speaking out loud rather than in my head. END
BEGIN NOW (Ive never talked or walked in my sleep.) END
BEGIN NOW T+5:00: Im woken up by some friends (they were not imaginary this time,) and we went downstairs to play some poker and then participate in a fraternity initiation ritual. END
BEGIN NOW The game had already started, and I was told to pick out my chips to buy in. END
BEGIN NOW Well, I counted out my chips and sat down at the table. END
BEGIN NOW Did you get your chips, F? END
BEGIN NOW I hear. END
BEGIN NOW Looking down, I see that there were no chips there. END
BEGIN NOW Embarrassed, I got up and counted out the chips again. END
BEGIN NOW I played five or so hands, but had a very difficult time reading the cards, and often made poor bets because I saw a four of hearts when it was really a five of diamonds. END
BEGIN NOW The ritual began, and I spent most of the time with my head down, testing the dreamlands once again. END
BEGIN NOW I took to having the same dream over and over again, in which I pick up a golden hexagonal prism. END
BEGIN NOW Each time, I tried to awaken still holding the box, but of course my fist was always tightly clenched around nothing. END
BEGIN NOW T+7:00: The ritual ends, and Ive finally managed to get to bed. END
BEGIN NOW The dreams are growing longer and more difficult to awaken from, and I think the effects are starting to wear off. END
BEGIN NOW T+9:00: I wake up again to lead another ritual, but Im so delirious at this point that Im unable to speak much and (for all I know) really frightening the pledges. END
BEGIN NOW Mercifully the ritual does not take much time at all, and Im able to return to bed. END
BEGIN NOW Although the sleep is fitful, I manage to fall into normal rest. END
BEGIN NOW T+15:00: The major effects are long gone, but I still feel slightly irritated. END
BEGIN NOW I have quite severe nearsightedness under normal circumstances, hovering around 20/100 in both eyes. END
