BEGIN NOW I'll cut the other 2 days out, as it's already been a fairly verbose story. END
BEGIN NOW I shall summarize some though. END
BEGIN NOW Everyone was worried about us, they thought we were never coming down, and to be fair, neither did we. END
BEGIN NOW We saw Dr. Seuss creatures in trees, elves, gnomes, dwarves, pixies, demons, golems, all kinds of 
mythical/demonic/spiritual creatures. END
BEGIN NOW And everything Drew saw, I saw, and vice versa. END
BEGIN NOW We ran over a ghost with a car. END
BEGIN NOW Digital clocks would make Tamagachi-like animations. END
BEGIN NOW It looked 8-bit. END
BEGIN NOW The auditory hallucinations did stop after the first night, the visuals mostly after the third night. END
BEGIN NOW On the third day, me, Drew, and a group of our friends went into a gazebo (a usual smoking spot) in a garden to smoke. END
BEGIN NOW I saw gnomes having sex in the trees. END
BEGIN NOW Little creatures would slowly bring antennas up out of bushes, and whenever Drew and I would compare what we saw, our friends were like 'That's not fucking there! END
BEGIN NOW Stop it!' END
BEGIN NOW A train went by (we weren't that far from the tracks) and an obese naked woman was having sex with a tree just outside the garden Every time she went 'down' the train blew it's horn. END
BEGIN NOW The train was actually there, our friends acknowledged that. END
BEGIN NOW It was uncanny. END
BEGIN NOW She would stay down for three seconds, and the train would blow for three seconds. END
BEGIN NOW This experience has made me think about it every time I hear a train. END
BEGIN NOW I ran into J a few days later, and he thought we had never left. END
BEGIN NOW He hung out with 'us' all throughout the night. END
BEGIN NOW Also, amazingly, Drew's parents, who were actually there the entire time, had no idea we were on anything. END
BEGIN NOW I don't know how, we were talking to people who weren't there, basically in front of them. END
BEGIN NOW We were lucky in that respect. END
BEGIN NOW Afterthoughts: First of all, I'd like to say: DO NOT TAKE JIMSON WEED. END
BEGIN NOW 99.99% of everyone should never take this. END
BEGIN NOW It's all too common for someone to get arrested or end up in a psyche ward, or even get shot from walking into someone else's house, not knowing what's going on. END
BEGIN NOW It's also very easy to be poisoned to death, people have died from it before. END
BEGIN NOW Also, you will be tested by the spirit(s), and if you fail, there can be dire consequences, particularly with the protector/wolf. END
BEGIN NOW It's not a pleasant high. END
BEGIN NOW In fact there is no 'high.' END
BEGIN NOW I felt completely normal, despite the craziness I witnessed. END
BEGIN NOW It was kind of amazing I remembered taking anything at all, that's not common. END
BEGIN NOW I didn't really think twice about what I was seeing, just like I probably don't in a dream. END
BEGIN NOW This is clearly a NEGATIVE PLANE OF EXISTENCE. END
BEGIN NOW I don't know if I believe in Hell, but if there is one, this is realm surely has some kind of correlation. END
BEGIN NOW Also, it has been said that Datura seeks you out, not the other way around. END
BEGIN NOW I deeply believe this to be true, and I believe that I was seeked out. END
BEGIN NOW I think J and Drew were caught in the crosshairs. END
BEGIN NOW To say this was just all in our minds is hard to justify. END
BEGIN NOW We interacted with people who weren't there simultaneously, witnessed the same things, and saw in blaring detail clearer images through binoculars. END
BEGIN NOW I omitted much of what happened, largely because of length, and largely because much of what I experienced I consider sacred, particularly some of the conversations. END
BEGIN NOW Not holy per se, but sacred. END
BEGIN NOW Also, I've found that the first encounter with an entheogen/ally sets the tone for the rest of the relationship. END
BEGIN NOW Toloache still visits me periodically in my dreams. END
BEGIN NOW All in all, I am glad I experienced this, as I learned much, particularly about the nature of reality/realities. END
