BEGIN NOW The Entree: 

25 finely chewed seeds of Datura Stramonium, aged to racemize the hyoscyamine to atropine and the scopolamine to atroscine. END
BEGIN NOW Each seed is roughly 7-8 mgs, but alkaloid content of each seed varies too much to be consistent. END
BEGIN NOW 2 bowls of Blueberry Kush, cured to decarboxylate the THCA, and smoked approximately two hours after ingestion of the Datura. END
BEGIN NOW I eye the small cluster of black, teardrop-shaped seeds in the palm of my hand with a mix of apprehension and usual pre-trip anxiety. END
BEGIN NOW They taste bitter with a hint of an earthy bite; not bad by any means but the hard husks get stuck in my teeth. END
BEGIN NOW I chew well and let the mass sit in my mouth for a few minutes to aid any sublingual absorption, and prepare to joyously delve into the bowels of torment and despair. END
BEGIN NOW The Trip: 

Eyes closed, pitch blackness. END
BEGIN NOW A sense of evil, a seductively malevolent vibe. END
BEGIN NOW Apprehension as the gears of my perspective slowly creak into the lower planes. END
BEGIN NOW Streaking spirals of light, growing brighter and brighter until... suddenly, break through. END
BEGIN NOW People and landscapes in perfect clarity as if I were watching through an invisible camera. END
BEGIN NOW A man turns towards his wife before stabbing her violently in the back. END
BEGIN NOW He rips the peeling flesh from her body as insects suddenly pour out. END
BEGIN NOW Cut. END
BEGIN NOW A pool of blood, undulating with red waves. END
BEGIN NOW Body parts falling in, silently splashing. END
BEGIN NOW No sound whatsoever to these visions. END
BEGIN NOW Cut. END
BEGIN NOW A wolf, black eyes, digging into an unidentifiable corpse. END
BEGIN NOW Strings of meat are dangling between its teeth. END
BEGIN NOW Cut. END
BEGIN NOW Many scenes of erotica, usually ending in gory climax. END
BEGIN NOW My skull is but a padded cell, the walls of which my inner demons bounce off. END
BEGIN NOW Themes of sadomasochism, violence punctuated by guilty pleasure. END
BEGIN NOW I hear sounds of sheer chaos. END
BEGIN NOW Screams, thumps. END
BEGIN NOW Dragging noises. END
BEGIN NOW Someone calling my name, louder, and louder. END
BEGIN NOW A gentle hiss and a bump. END
BEGIN NOW Cut. END
BEGIN NOW Spiders. END
BEGIN NOW Lots of spiders, pouring through the cracks of reality as if puncturing through this thin veil of ordinary life. END
BEGIN NOW I feel things gently running over my body. END
BEGIN NOW I don't open my eyes. END
BEGIN NOW Cut. END
BEGIN NOW Swinging bodies on nooses, burning. END
BEGIN NOW Fire, blood dripping as maggots squirm into the quivering flesh. END
BEGIN NOW I am carrying on a conversation with something, but I do not know what. END
BEGIN NOW My mind echoes with distorted fragments of meaning; snippets of grand truth ripped from this primeval chaos. END
BEGIN NOW Lots of blood. END
BEGIN NOW Death. END
